content:
Customize the Embedded Chat Offline Form

Allow customers to submit a case form with Embedded Chat when your support agents are offline. Customize the form depending on your business use case. Choose which fields appear, change the order, and mark certain fields as required.

To set up an offline support form:

From Setup, enter Embedded Service, select Embedded Service Deployments.
Click Edit next to Chat Settings.
In the Offline support section, move the radio button to Active.
Click Edit.
Select a Case record type.
Select the fields shown on the form.
Change the order of the fields using the up and down arrow.
Add a field by clicking +. You can add only fields that are available on the object.
Remove a field by clicking X.
Require customers to fill out a field by selecting Required next to the field.

Optionally, enter a URL for the offline support header image.

To create custom field names in your offline form:

From Setup, enter Rename Tabs and Labels, select Rename Tabs and Labels.
Set your primary deployment language from the Select Language dropdown list.
Select Edit next to the Cases tab option. Enter the singular and plural forms of the new tab name. Save your changes.

IMPORTANT Before you start, enable Web-to-Case and turn on the “Enable Support QuickAction Rest endpoint for Guest Users” permission for your org.

To turn off your offline support form at any time, view your deployment in Setup and move the Offline support slider to Inactive. Refresh and repaste the code snippet into your website each time you turn offline support on or off.
title: Customizing Embedded Chat Offline Forms
